title: Print, "Receuil de Fontaines", 1703–70
inscribed:
The number 2 is inscribed in graphite in the lower center of the image.
Imprinted in the lower left margin are the words "F.Boucher. In." Imprinted in the lower right margin are the words "Huquier, ex."
creditline: Purchased for the Museum by the Advisory Council
description: Rococo design with two tritons amongst a number of large shells with water flowing
